						<div class="postbody">Reading the notes and preparing/assigning the instruments and doing other bookkeeping can be broken up across frames. In my case, it saved about ~450 cycles.<br /><br />Reading the sequences and writing the APU registers has to be done every frame. I didn't implement any instrument compression, so that's a pretty big speed advantage over libraries that do.</div>

